Essentially, itâ€™s a process of solving complex mathematical puzzles. Miners are the most important part of every cryptocurrency community, as they not only mark transactions as legitimate, theyâ€™re also responsible for putting new tokens into circulations.

Miners receive substantial rewards for successfully mining a block of transactions. In the Bitcoin Cash network, the reward currently stands at 12.5 BCH per block + all the transaction fees within said block.

